More than 25 village groups from Bumula have received a grant of Sh2 million to uplift residents&rsquo; livelihoods.The cheques from the Central Organisation of Micro Credit Villages were presented during the launch of the Bumula Ward Micro Development Villages.COMCV supervisor Joseph Amunga said the money should be spent wisely to improve living standards and assist in the realisation of Vision 2030.The initiative brings together youths, women and self-help groups in Bumula ward and is being undertaken in wards nationwide. Bumula is the pilot project in Bungoma county.